123inline bool IsSubsurfaceShadingModel(FMaterialShadingModelField ShadingModel)
124{
125 return ShadingModel.HasShadingModel(MSM_Subsurface) || ShadingModel.HasShadingModel(MSM_PreintegratedSkin) ||
126 ShadingModel.HasShadingModel(MSM_SubsurfaceProfile) || ShadingModel.HasShadingModel(MSM_TwoSidedFoliage) ||
127 ShadingModel.HasShadingModel(MSM_Cloth) || ShadingModel.HasShadingModel(MSM_Eye);
128}
129
130inline bool UseSubsurfaceProfile(FMaterialShadingModelField ShadingModel)
131{
132 return ShadingModel.HasShadingModel(MSM_SubsurfaceProfile) || ShadingModel.HasShadingModel(MSM_Eye);
133}
134
135inline uint32 GetUseSubsurfaceProfileShadingModelMask()
136{
137 return (1 << MSM_SubsurfaceProfile) | (1 << MSM_Eye);
138}

205/** @return the number of components in a vector type. */
206inline uint32 GetNumComponents(EMaterialValueType Type)
207{
208 switch (Type)
209 {
210 case MCT_UInt:
211 case MCT_UInt1:
212 case MCT_Float:
213 case MCT_Float1: return 1;
214 case MCT_UInt2:
215 case MCT_Float2: return 2;
216 case MCT_UInt3:
217 case MCT_Float3: return 3;
218 case MCT_UInt4:
219 case MCT_Float4: return 4;
220 case MCT_LWCScalar: return 1;
221 case MCT_LWCVector2: return 2;
222 case MCT_LWCVector3: return 3;
223 case MCT_LWCVector4: return 4;
224 case MCT_StaticBool: return 1;
225 case MCT_Bool: return 1;
226 default: return 0;
227 }
228}
229
230inline bool IsMaterialValueType(EMaterialValueType InType, EMaterialValueType InCompare)
231{
232 return (InType & InCompare) != 0;
233}
234
235inline bool IsLWCType(EMaterialValueType InType)
236{
237 return IsMaterialValueType(InType, MCT_LWCType);
238}
239
240inline bool IsFloatNumericType(EMaterialValueType InType)
241{
242 return IsMaterialValueType(InType, EMaterialValueType(MCT_Float | MCT_LWCType));
243}
244
245inline bool IsUIntNumericType(EMaterialValueType InType)
246{
247 return IsMaterialValueType(InType, MCT_UInt);
248}
249
250inline bool IsNumericType(EMaterialValueType InType)
251{
252 // 'ShadingModel' is considered an 'int'
253 return IsMaterialValueType(InType, EMaterialValueType(MCT_Float | MCT_LWCType | MCT_UInt | MCT_ShadingModel));
254}
255
256inline bool IsPrimitiveType(EMaterialValueType InType)
257{
258 // 'ShadingModel' is considered an 'int'
259 return IsMaterialValueType(InType, EMaterialValueType(MCT_Float | MCT_LWCType | MCT_UInt | MCT_ShadingModel | MCT_Bool | MCT_StaticBool));
260}
261
262inline EMaterialValueType MakeNonLWCType(EMaterialValueType Type)
263{
264 switch (Type)
265 {
266 case MCT_LWCScalar: return MCT_Float1;
267 case MCT_LWCVector2: return MCT_Float2;
268 case MCT_LWCVector3: return MCT_Float3;
269 case MCT_LWCVector4: return MCT_Float4;
270 default: return Type;
271 }
272}
273
274inline EMaterialValueType MakeLWCType(EMaterialValueType Type)
275{
276 switch (Type)
277 {
278 case MCT_Float: return MCT_LWCScalar;
279 case MCT_Float1: return MCT_LWCScalar;
280 case MCT_Float2: return MCT_LWCVector2;
281 case MCT_Float3: return MCT_LWCVector3;
282 case MCT_Float4: return MCT_LWCVector4;
283 default: return Type;
284 }
285}

377class FMaterialVirtualTextureStack
378{
379 DECLARE_TYPE_LAYOUT(FMaterialVirtualTextureStack, NonVirtual);
380public:
381 FMaterialVirtualTextureStack();
382 /** Construct with a texture index when this references a preallocated VT stack (for example when we are using a URuntimeVirtualTexture). */
383 FMaterialVirtualTextureStack(int32 InPreallocatedStackTextureIndex);
384
385 /** Add space for a layer in the stack. Returns an index that can be used for SetLayer(). */
386 uint32 AddLayer();
387 /** Set an expression index at a layer in the stack. */
388 uint32 SetLayer(int32 LayerIndex, int32 UniformExpressionIndex);
389 /** Get the number of layers allocated in the stack. */
390 inline uint32 GetNumLayers() const { return NumLayers; }
391 /** Returns true if we have allocated the maximum number of layers for this stack. */
392 inline bool AreLayersFull() const { return NumLayers == VIRTUALTEXTURE_SPACE_MAXLAYERS; }
393 /** Find the layer in the stack that was set with this expression index. */
394 int32 FindLayer(int32 UniformExpressionIndex) const;
395
396 /** Returns true if this is a stack that with a preallocated layout of layers (for example when we are using a URuntimeVirtualTexture). */
397 inline bool IsPreallocatedStack() const { return PreallocatedStackTextureIndex != INDEX_NONE; }
398 /** Get the array of UTexture objects for the expressions that in the layers of this stack. Can return nullptr objects for layers that don't hold UTexture2D references. */
399 void GetTextureValues(const FMaterialRenderContext& Context, const FUniformExpressionSet& UniformExpressionSet, UTexture const** OutValues) const;
400 /** Get the URuntimeVirtualTexture object if one was used to initialize this stack. */
401 void GetTextureValue(const FMaterialRenderContext& Context, const FUniformExpressionSet& UniformExpressionSet, const URuntimeVirtualTexture*& OutValue) const;
402 /** Get the USparseVolumeTexture object if one was used to initialize this stack. */
403 void GetTextureValue(const FMaterialRenderContext& Context, const FUniformExpressionSet& UniformExpressionSet, const USparseVolumeTexture * &OutValue) const;
404
405 void Serialize(FArchive& Ar);
406
407 friend FArchive& operator<<(FArchive& Ar, FMaterialVirtualTextureStack& Stack)
408 {
409 Stack.Serialize(Ar);
410 return Ar;
411 }
412
413 friend bool operator==(const FMaterialVirtualTextureStack& Lhs, const FMaterialVirtualTextureStack& Rhs)
414 {
415 if (Lhs.PreallocatedStackTextureIndex != Rhs.PreallocatedStackTextureIndex || Lhs.NumLayers != Rhs.NumLayers)
416 {
417 return false;
418 }
419 for (uint32 i = 0u; i < Lhs.NumLayers; ++i)
420 {
421 if (Lhs.LayerUniformExpressionIndices[i] != Rhs.LayerUniformExpressionIndices[i])
422 {
423 return false;
424 }
425 }
426 return true;
427 }
428
429 friend inline bool operator!=(const FMaterialVirtualTextureStack& Lhs, const FMaterialVirtualTextureStack& Rhs)
430 {
431 return !operator==(Lhs, Rhs);
432 }
433
434 /** Number of layers that have been allocated in this stack. */
435 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint32, NumLayers);
436 /** Indices of the expressions that were set to layers in this stack. */
437 LAYOUT_ARRAY(int32, LayerUniformExpressionIndices, VIRTUALTEXTURE_SPACE_MAXLAYERS);
438 /** Index of a texture reference if we create a stack from a single known texture that has it's own layer stack. */
439 LAYOUT_FIELD(int32, PreallocatedStackTextureIndex);
440};
441
442/**
443* Represents the evaluation of a material parameter directly to a byte offset in the preshader uniform buffer.
444* A UniformParameterEvaluation avoids the overhead of executing an entire preshader when all it does is
445* evaluate a parameter with a single instruction.
446*/
447class FMaterialUniformParameterEvaluation
448{
449 DECLARE_TYPE_LAYOUT(FMaterialUniformParameterEvaluation, NonVirtual);
450public:
451 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint16, ParameterIndex); /** Index of the parameter for UniformExpressionSet::GetNumericParameter() */
452 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint16, BufferOffset); /** Offset in the preshader uniform buffer (in bytes) where result will be written */
453};
454
455class FMaterialUniformPreshaderField
456{
457 DECLARE_TYPE_LAYOUT(FMaterialUniformPreshaderField, NonVirtual);
458public:
459 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint32, BufferOffset); /** Offset in the uniform buffer where result will be written */
460 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint32, ComponentIndex);
461 LAYOUT_FIELD(UE::Shader::EValueType, Type);
462};
463
464class FMaterialUniformPreshaderHeader
465{
466 DECLARE_TYPE_LAYOUT(FMaterialUniformPreshaderHeader, NonVirtual);
467public:
468 friend inline bool operator==(const FMaterialUniformPreshaderHeader& Lhs, const FMaterialUniformPreshaderHeader& Rhs)
469 {
470 return Lhs.OpcodeOffset == Rhs.OpcodeOffset &&
471 Lhs.OpcodeSize == Rhs.OpcodeSize &&
472 Lhs.FieldIndex == Rhs.FieldIndex &&
473 Lhs.NumFields == Rhs.NumFields;
474 }
475 friend inline bool operator!=(const FMaterialUniformPreshaderHeader& Lhs, const FMaterialUniformPreshaderHeader& Rhs)
476 {
477 return !operator==(Lhs, Rhs);
478 }
479
480 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint32, OpcodeOffset); /** Offset of the preshader opcodes, within the material's buffer */
481 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint32, OpcodeSize); /** Size of the preshader opcodes */
482 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint32, FieldIndex);
483 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint32, NumFields);
484};

584class FUniformParameterOverrides
585{
586public:
587 void SetNumericOverride(EMaterialParameterType Type, const FHashedMaterialParameterInfo& ParameterInfo, const UE::Shader::FValue& Value, bool bOverride);

595 struct FNumericParameterKey
596 {
597 FHashedMaterialParameterInfo ParameterInfo;
598 EMaterialParameterType ParameterType;
599
600 friend inline bool operator==(const FNumericParameterKey& Lhs, const FNumericParameterKey& Rhs)
601 {
602 return Lhs.ParameterInfo == Rhs.ParameterInfo && Lhs.ParameterType == Rhs.ParameterType;
603 }
604 friend inline bool operator!=(const FNumericParameterKey& Lhs, const FNumericParameterKey& Rhs)
605 {
606 return !operator==(Lhs, Rhs);
607 }
608 friend inline uint32 GetTypeHash(const FNumericParameterKey& Value)
609 {
610 return HashCombine(GetTypeHash(Value.ParameterInfo), GetTypeHash(Value.ParameterType));
611 }
612 };

616 struct FTextureParameterKey
617 {
618 FHashedMaterialParameterInfo ParameterInfo;

620
621 friend inline bool operator==(const FTextureParameterKey& Lhs, const FTextureParameterKey& Rhs)
622 {
623 return Lhs.ParameterInfo == Rhs.ParameterInfo && Lhs.TextureIndex == Rhs.TextureIndex;
624 }
625 friend inline bool operator!=(const FTextureParameterKey& Lhs, const FTextureParameterKey& Rhs)
626 {
627 return !operator==(Lhs, Rhs);
628 }
629 friend inline uint32 GetTypeHash(const FTextureParameterKey& Value)
630 {
631 return HashCombine(GetTypeHash(Value.ParameterInfo), GetTypeHash(Value.TextureIndex));
632 }
633 };

639/** Stores all uniform expressions for a material generated from a material translation. */
640class FUniformExpressionSet
641{
642 DECLARE_TYPE_LAYOUT(FUniformExpressionSet, NonVirtual);
643public:
644 FUniformExpressionSet() : UniformPreshaderBufferSize(0u) {}
645
646 bool IsEmpty() const;
647 bool operator==(const FUniformExpressionSet& ReferenceSet) const;

800
801 bool IsSceneTextureUsed(ESceneTextureId TexId) const { return (UsedSceneTextures & (1 << TexId)) != 0; }
802
803 void SetIsSceneTextureUsed(ESceneTextureId TexId)
804 {
805 // User scene textures aren't added to used bits -- those are stored separately in UserSceneTextureInputs
806 if (TexId < PPI_UserSceneTexture0)
807 {
808 UsedSceneTextures |= (1 << TexId);
809 }
810 }
811
812#if WITH_EDITOR
813 // Returns Id for a user scene texture input, or INDEX_NONE if allocation fails.
814 int32 FindOrAddUserSceneTexture(FName UserSceneTexture);
815
816 // Returns number of post process inputs used, between PostProcessInput SceneTexture nodes and UserSceneTexture nodes. If this exceeds
817 // kPostProcessMaterialInputCountMax, compile should be failed (number is returned rather than bool for error reporting purposes).
818 int32 GetNumPostProcessInputsUsed() const;
819#endif // WITH_EDITOR
820
821 void SetIsDBufferTextureUsed(int32 TextureIndex) { UsedDBufferTextures |= (1 << TextureIndex); }
822 void SetIsDBufferTextureLookupUsed(bool bValue) { bUsesDBufferTextureLookup = bValue; }
823
824 void SetIsPathTracingBufferTextureUsed(int32 TexId) { UsedPathTracingBufferTextures |= (1 << TexId); }
825
826 /** Indicates whether the material uses scene color. */
827 bool RequiresSceneColorCopy() const { return IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_SceneColor); }
828
829 /** true if the material uses any GBuffer textures */
830 bool NeedsGBuffer() const
831 {
832 return
833 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_DiffuseColor) ||
834 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_SpecularColor) ||
835 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_SubsurfaceColor) ||
836 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_BaseColor) ||
837 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_Specular) ||
838 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_Metallic) ||
839 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_WorldNormal) ||
840 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_WorldTangent) ||
841 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_Opacity) ||
842 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_Roughness) ||
843 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_Anisotropy) ||
844 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_MaterialAO) ||
845 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_DecalMask) ||
846 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_ShadingModelColor) ||
847 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_ShadingModelID) ||
848 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_StoredBaseColor) ||
849 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_StoredSpecular) ||
850 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_Velocity) ||
851 IsSceneTextureUsed(PPI_IsFirstPerson);
852 }

894

896 LAYOUT_FIELD(uint8, RuntimeVirtualTextureOutputAttributeMask);

926 LAYOUT_BITFIELD(uint8, bUsesVertexInterpolator, 1);

960/**
961 * Usage options for a shader map.
962 * The purpose of EMaterialShaderMapUsage is to allow creating a unique yet deterministic (no appCreateGuid) Id,
963 * For a shader map corresponding to any UMaterial or UMaterialInstance, for different use cases.
964 * As an example, when exporting a material to Lightmass we want to compile a shader map with FLightmassMaterialProxy,
965 * And generate a FMaterialShaderMapId for it that allows reuse later, so it must be deterministic.
966 */
967namespace EMaterialShaderMapUsage
968{
969 enum Type
970 {
971 Default,
972 LightmassExportEmissive,
973 LightmassExportDiffuse,
974 LightmassExportOpacity,
975 LightmassExportNormal,
976 MaterialExportBaseColor,
977 MaterialExportSpecular,
978 MaterialExportNormal,
979 MaterialExportTangent,
980 MaterialExportMetallic,
981 MaterialExportRoughness,
982 MaterialExportAnisotropy,
983 MaterialExportAO,
984 MaterialExportEmissive,
985 MaterialExportOpacity,
986 MaterialExportOpacityMask,
987 MaterialExportSubSurfaceColor,
988 MaterialExportClearCoat,
989 MaterialExportClearCoatRoughness,
990 MaterialExportCustomOutput,
991 MaterialExportShadingModel,
992 MaterialExportRefraction,
993 };
994}

1118/** Contains all the information needed to uniquely identify a FMaterialShaderMap. */
1119class FMaterialShaderMapId
1120{
1121public:
1122 FSHAHash CookedShaderMapIdHash;
1123
1124#if WITH_EDITOR
1125 /**
1126 * The base material's StateId.
1127 * This guid represents all the state of a UMaterial that is not covered by the other members of FMaterialShaderMapId.
1128 * Any change to the UMaterial that modifies that state (for example, adding an expression) must modify this guid.
1129 */
1130 FGuid BaseMaterialId;
1131#endif
1132
1133 /**
1134 * Quality level that this shader map is going to be compiled at.
1135 * Can be a value of EMaterialQualityLevel::Num if quality level doesn't matter to the compiled result.
1136 */
1137 EMaterialQualityLevel::Type QualityLevel;
1138
1139 /** Feature level that the shader map is going to be compiled for. */
1140 ERHIFeatureLevel::Type FeatureLevel;
1141
1142#if WITH_EDITOR
1143 /**
1144 * Indicates what use case this shader map will be for.
1145 * This allows the same UMaterial / UMaterialInstance to be compiled with multiple FMaterial derived classes,
1146 * While still creating an Id that is deterministic between runs (no appCreateGuid used).
1147 */
1148 EMaterialShaderMapUsage::Type Usage;
1149
1150 /**
1151 * Name of which specific custom output this shader map will be a use case for. Only used if Usage is MaterialExportCustomOutput.
1152 */
1153 FString UsageCustomOutput;
1154
1155private:
1156 /** Was the shadermap Id loaded in from a cooked resource. */
1157 bool bIsCookedId;
1158
1159 /** Relevant portions of StaticParameterSet from material. */
1160 TArray<FStaticSwitchParameter> StaticSwitchParameters;
1161 TArray<FStaticComponentMaskParameter> StaticComponentMaskParameters;
1162 TArray<FStaticTerrainLayerWeightParameter> TerrainLayerWeightParameters;
1163 TOptional<FMaterialLayersFunctions::ID> MaterialLayersId;
1164public:
1165 /** Guids of any functions the material was dependent on. */
1166 TArray<FGuid> ReferencedFunctions;
1167
1168 /** Guids of any Parameter Collections the material was dependent on. */
1169 TArray<FGuid> ReferencedParameterCollections;
1170
1171 /** Shader types of shaders that are inlined in this shader map in the DDC. */
1172 TArray<FShaderTypeDependency> ShaderTypeDependencies;
1173
1174 /** Shader pipeline types of shader pipelines that are inlined in this shader map in the DDC. */
1175 TArray<FShaderPipelineTypeDependency> ShaderPipelineTypeDependencies;
1176
1177 /** Vertex factory types of shaders that are inlined in this shader map in the DDC. */
1178 TArray<FVertexFactoryTypeDependency> VertexFactoryTypeDependencies;
1179
1180 /**
1181 * Hash of the textures referenced by the uniform expressions in the shader map.
1182 * This is stored in the shader map Id to gracefully handle situations where code changes
1183 * that generates the array of textures that the uniform expressions use to link up after being loaded from the DDC.
1184 */
1185 FSHAHash TextureReferencesHash;
1186
1187 /** A hash of the content of files (dynamically) included by material expressions. */
1188 FSHAHash ExpressionIncludesHash;
1189
1190 /** A hash of the base property overrides for this material instance. */
1191 FSHAHash BasePropertyOverridesHash;
1192
1193 /** A hash of all external code delcarations referenced in the shader map. */
1194 FSHAHash ExternalCodeReferencesHash;
1195
1196 /** Is the material using the new HLSL generator? */
1197 bool bUsingNewHLSLGenerator;
1198
1199 /** The Substrate configuration used when compiling this material, can be tweaked in the material editor for live visualization of simplification. */
1200 FSubstrateCompilationConfig SubstrateCompilationConfig;
1201
1202#endif // WITH_EDITOR
1203
1204 /*
1205 * Type layout parameters of the memory image
1206 */
1207 FPlatformTypeLayoutParameters LayoutParams;
1208
1209 FMaterialShaderMapId()
1210 : QualityLevel(EMaterialQualityLevel::High)
1211 , FeatureLevel(ERHIFeatureLevel::SM5)
1212#if WITH_EDITOR
1213 , Usage(EMaterialShaderMapUsage::Default)
1214 , bIsCookedId(false)
1215 , bUsingNewHLSLGenerator(false)
1216 , SubstrateCompilationConfig()
1217#endif
1218 { }
1219
1220 ~FMaterialShaderMapId()
1221 { }
1222
1223#if WITH_EDITOR
1224 ENGINE_API void SetShaderDependencies(const TArray<FShaderType*>& ShaderTypes, const TArray<const FShaderPipelineType*>& ShaderPipelineTypes, const TArray<FVertexFactoryType*>& VFTypes, EShaderPlatform ShaderPlatform);
1225#endif
1226
1227 void Serialize(FArchive& Ar, bool bLoadingCooked);
1228
1229 bool IsCookedId() const
1230 {
1231#if WITH_EDITOR
1232 return bIsCookedId;
1233#else
1234 return true;
1235#endif
1236 }
1237
1238 bool IsValid() const
1239 {
1240#if WITH_EDITOR
1241 return !IsCookedId() ? BaseMaterialId.IsValid() : (CookedShaderMapIdHash != FSHAHash());
1242#else
1243 return (CookedShaderMapIdHash != FSHAHash());
1244#endif
1245 }
1246
1247 friend uint32 GetTypeHash(const FMaterialShaderMapId& Ref)
1248 {
1249#if WITH_EDITOR
1250 return !Ref.IsCookedId() ? Ref.BaseMaterialId.A : (*(uint32*)&Ref.CookedShaderMapIdHash.Hash[0]);
1251#else
1252 // Using the hash value directly instead of FSHAHash CRC as fairly uniform distribution
1253 return *(uint32*)&Ref.CookedShaderMapIdHash.Hash[0];
1254#endif
1255 }
1256
1257 SIZE_T GetSizeBytes() const
1258 {
1259 return sizeof(*this)
1260#if WITH_EDITOR
1261 + ReferencedFunctions.GetAllocatedSize()
1262 + ReferencedParameterCollections.GetAllocatedSize()
1263 + ShaderTypeDependencies.GetAllocatedSize()
1264 + ShaderPipelineTypeDependencies.GetAllocatedSize()
1265 + VertexFactoryTypeDependencies.GetAllocatedSize()
1266#endif
1267 ;
1268 }
1269
1270#if WITH_EDITOR
1271 /** Hashes the material-specific part of this shader map Id. */
1272 ENGINE_API void GetMaterialHash(FSHAHash& OutHash, bool bWithStaticParameters) const;
1273
1274 void GetMaterialHash(FSHAHash& OutHash) const
1275 {
1276 GetMaterialHash(OutHash, true);
1277 }
1278#endif

1280 ENGINE_API bool Equals(const FMaterialShaderMapId& ReferenceSet, bool bWithStaticParameters) const;

1283 * Tests this set against another for equality
1284 *
1285 * @param ReferenceSet The set to compare against
1286 * @return true if the sets are equal
1287 */
1288 bool operator==(const FMaterialShaderMapId& ReferenceSet) const
1289 {
1290 return Equals(ReferenceSet, true);
1291 }
1292
1293 bool operator!=(const FMaterialShaderMapId& ReferenceSet) const
1294 {
1295 return !Equals(ReferenceSet, true);
1296 }
1297

1299 bool IsContentValid() const;
1300
1301 inline EShaderPermutationFlags GetPermutationFlags() const { return GetShaderPermutationFlags(LayoutParams); }
1302

1328#endif // WITH_EDITOR

1384 inline uint32 GetNumShaders() const
1385 {
1386 uint32 NumShaders = Super::GetNumShaders();
1387 for (FMeshMaterialShaderMap* MeshShaderMap : OrderedMeshShaderMaps)
1388 {
1389 NumShaders += MeshShaderMap->GetNumShaders();
1390 }
1391 return NumShaders;
1392 }

1395 {
1396 uint32 NumPipelines = Super::GetNumShaderPipelines();
1397 for (FMeshMaterialShaderMap* MeshShaderMap : OrderedMeshShaderMaps)
1398 {
1399 NumPipelines += MeshShaderMap->GetNumShaderPipelines();
1400 }
1401 return NumPipelines;
1402 }

1490 // ShaderMap interface
1491 TShaderRef<FShader> GetShader(FShaderType* ShaderType, int32 PermutationId = 0) const
1492 {
1493 FShader* Shader = GetContent()->GetShader(ShaderType, PermutationId);
1494 return Shader ? TShaderRef<FShader>(Shader, *this) : TShaderRef<FShader>();
1495 }
1496 template<typename ShaderType> TShaderRef<ShaderType> GetShader(int32 PermutationId = 0) const
1497 {
1498 return TShaderRef<ShaderType>::Cast(GetShader(&ShaderType::GetStaticType(), PermutationId));
1499 }
1500 template<typename ShaderType> TShaderRef<ShaderType> GetShader(const typename ShaderType::FPermutationDomain& PermutationVector) const
1501 {
1502 return TShaderRef<ShaderType>::Cast(GetShader(&ShaderType::GetStaticType(), PermutationVector.ToDimensionValueId()));
1503 }

1690 bool IsValidForRendering(bool bFailOnInvalid = false) const
1691 {
1692#if 0
1693 // Any material being used for rendering should be frozen, and successfully compiled
1694 // Compiliation may not be finalized yet, if the shader map is still compiling
1695 const bool bValid = bCompiledSuccessfully && GetFrozenContentSize() > 0u;
1696 // && !bDeletedThroughDeferredCleanup; //deferred actually deletion will prevent the material to go away before we finish rendering
1697#endif
1698 const bool bValid = GetFrozenContentSize() > 0u;
1699
1700 checkf(bValid || !bFailOnInvalid, TEXT("FMaterialShaderMap %s invalid for rendering: bCompilationFinalized: %i, bCompiledSuccessfully: %i, bDeletedThroughDeferredCleanup: %i, FrozenContentSize: %d"), GetFriendlyName(),
1701 bCompilationFinalized, bCompiledSuccessfully, bDeletedThroughDeferredCleanup ? 1 : 0, GetFrozenContentSize());
1702 return bValid;
1703 }

1711 void CountNumShaders(int32& NumShaders, int32& NumPipelines) const
1712 {
1713 NumShaders = GetContent()->GetNumShaders();
1714 NumPipelines = GetContent()->GetNumShaderPipelines();
1715
1716 for (FMeshMaterialShaderMap* MeshShaderMap : GetContent()->OrderedMeshShaderMaps)
1717 {
1718 if (MeshShaderMap)
1719 {
1720 NumShaders += MeshShaderMap->GetNumShaders();
1721 NumPipelines += MeshShaderMap->GetNumShaderPipelines();
1722 }
1723 }
1724 }

1743 /**
1744 * A global map from a material's static parameter set to any shader map cached for that material.
1745 * Note: this does not necessarily contain all material shader maps in memory. Shader maps with the same key can evict each other.
1746 * No ref counting needed as these are removed on destruction of the shader map.

1748 static TMap<FMaterialShaderMapId,FMaterialShaderMap*> GIdToMaterialShaderMap[SP_NumPlatforms];

1827/** Flags that define the behavior of material translation validation. */
1828enum class EMaterialTranslateValidationFlags : uint32
1829{
1830 None = 0,
1831 Strict_RuntimeVirtualTexture = 1 << 0,
1832};
1833ENUM_CLASS_FLAGS(EMaterialTranslateValidationFlags)
1834
1835/**
1836 * Enum that contains entries for the ways that material properties need to be compiled.
1837 * This 'inherits' from EMaterialProperty in the sense that all of its values start after the values in EMaterialProperty.
1838 * Each material property is compiled once for its usual shader frequency, determined by GetShaderFrequency(),
1839 * And then this enum contains entries for extra compiles of a material property with a different shader frequency.
1840 * This is necessary for material properties which need to be evaluated in multiple shader frequencies.
1841 */
1842enum ECompiledMaterialProperty
1843{
1844 CompiledMP_EmissiveColorCS = MP_MAX,
1845 CompiledMP_PrevWorldPositionOffset,
1846 CompiledMP_MAX
1847};
1848
1849/**
1850* Enum that contains entries for the ways that material properties can be compiled with partial derivative calculations.
1851* Standard material shaders using the automatic hardware FiniteDifferences, Nanite uses Analytic, and we will likely
1852* need to add a separate one for raytracing at a later date.
1853*/
1854enum ECompiledPartialDerivativeVariation
1855{
1856 CompiledPDV_FiniteDifferences,
1857 CompiledPDV_Analytic,
1858 CompiledPDV_MAX
1859};

1861/**
1862 * Uniquely identifies a material expression output.
1863 * Used by the material compiler to keep track of which output it is compiling.
1864 */
1865class FMaterialExpressionKey
1866{
1867public:
1868 UMaterialExpression* Expression;
1869 int32 OutputIndex;
1870 /** Attribute currently being compiled through a MatterialAttributes connection. */
1871 FGuid MaterialAttributeID;
1872 // Expressions are different (e.g. ResolvedView.PrevWorldViewOrigin) when using previous frame's values, value if from FHLSLMaterialTranslator::bCompilingPreviousFrame
1873 bool bCompilingPreviousFrameKey;
1874
1875 FMaterialExpressionKey(UMaterialExpression* InExpression, int32 InOutputIndex) :
1876 Expression(InExpression),
1877 OutputIndex(InOutputIndex),
1878 MaterialAttributeID(FGuid(0,0,0,0)),
1879 bCompilingPreviousFrameKey(false)
1880 {}
1881
1882 FMaterialExpressionKey(UMaterialExpression* InExpression, int32 InOutputIndex, const FGuid& InMaterialAttributeID, bool bInCompilingPreviousFrameKey) :
1883 Expression(InExpression),
1884 OutputIndex(InOutputIndex),
1885 MaterialAttributeID(InMaterialAttributeID),
1886 bCompilingPreviousFrameKey(bInCompilingPreviousFrameKey)
1887 {}
1888
1889
1890 friend bool operator==(const FMaterialExpressionKey& X, const FMaterialExpressionKey& Y)
1891 {
1892 return X.Expression == Y.Expression && X.OutputIndex == Y.OutputIndex && X.MaterialAttributeID == Y.MaterialAttributeID && X.bCompilingPreviousFrameKey == Y.bCompilingPreviousFrameKey;
1893 }
1894
1895 friend uint32 GetTypeHash(const FMaterialExpressionKey& ExpressionKey)
1896 {
1897 return PointerHash(ExpressionKey.Expression);
1898 }
1899};
1900
1901/** Function specific compiler state. */
1902class FMaterialFunctionCompileState
1903{
1904public:
1905 explicit FMaterialFunctionCompileState(UMaterialExpressionMaterialFunctionCall* InFunctionCall)
1906 : FunctionCall(InFunctionCall)
1907 {}
1908
1909 ~FMaterialFunctionCompileState()
1910 {
1911 ClearSharedFunctionStates();
1912 }
1913
1914 FMaterialFunctionCompileState* FindOrAddSharedFunctionState(FMaterialExpressionKey& ExpressionKey, class UMaterialExpressionMaterialFunctionCall* SharedFunctionCall)
1915 {
1916 if (FMaterialFunctionCompileState** ExistingState = SharedFunctionStates.Find(ExpressionKey))
1917 {
1918 return *ExistingState;
1919 }
1920 return SharedFunctionStates.Add(ExpressionKey, new FMaterialFunctionCompileState(SharedFunctionCall));
1921 }
1922
1923 void ClearSharedFunctionStates()
1924 {
1925 for (auto SavedStateIt = SharedFunctionStates.CreateIterator(); SavedStateIt; ++SavedStateIt)
1926 {
1927 FMaterialFunctionCompileState* SavedState = SavedStateIt.Value();
1928 SavedState->ClearSharedFunctionStates();
1929 delete SavedState;
1930 }
1931 SharedFunctionStates.Empty();
1932 }
1933
1934 void Reset()
1935 {
1936 ExpressionStack.Empty();
1937 ExpressionCodeMap.Empty();
1938 ClearSharedFunctionStates();
1939 }
1940
1941 class UMaterialExpressionMaterialFunctionCall* FunctionCall;
1942
1943 // Stack used to avoid re-entry within this function
1944 TArray<FMaterialExpressionKey> ExpressionStack;
1945
1946 /** A map from material expression to the index into CodeChunks of the code for the material expression. */
1947 TMap<FMaterialExpressionKey,int32> ExpressionCodeMap;
1948
1949 TMap<UMaterialExpression*, int32> ExecExpressionCodeMap;
1950
1951private:
1952 /** Cache of MaterialFunctionOutput CodeChunks. Allows for further reuse than just the ExpressionCodeMap */
1953 TMap<FMaterialExpressionKey, FMaterialFunctionCompileState*> SharedFunctionStates;
1954};

1969/**
1970 * FMaterial serves 3 intertwined purposes:
1971 * Represents a material to the material compilation process, and provides hooks for extensibility (CompileProperty, etc)
1972 * Represents a material to the renderer, with functions to access material properties
1973 * Stores a cached shader map, and other transient output from a compile, which is necessary with async shader compiling
1974 * (when a material finishes async compilation, the shader map and compile errors need to be stored somewhere)
1975 */
1976class FMaterial
1977{
1978public:
1979#if UE_CHECK_FMATERIAL_LIFETIME
1980 ENGINE_API uint32 AddRef() const;
1981 ENGINE_API uint32 Release() const;
1982 inline uint32 GetRefCount() const { return uint32(NumDebugRefs.GetValue()); }
1983
1984 mutable FThreadSafeCounter NumDebugRefs;
1985#else
1986 FORCEINLINE uint32 AddRef() const { return 0u; }
1987 FORCEINLINE uint32 Release() const { return 0u; }
1988 FORCEINLINE uint32 GetRefCount() const { return 0u; }
1989#endif
1990
1991 /** Sets shader maps on the specified materials without blocking. */
1992 ENGINE_API static void SetShaderMapsOnMaterialResources(const TMap<TRefCountPtr<FMaterial>, TRefCountPtr<FMaterialShaderMap>>& MaterialsToUpdate);
1993
1994 ENGINE_API static void DeferredDelete(FMaterial* Material);
1995
1996 ENGINE_API static void DeleteMaterialsOnRenderThread(TArray<TRefCountPtr<FMaterial>>& MaterialsRenderThread);
1997
1998 template<typename TMaterial>
1999 static void DeferredDeleteArray(TArray<TRefCountPtr<TMaterial>>& Materials)
2000 {
2001 if (Materials.Num() > 0)
2002 {
2003 TArray<TRefCountPtr<FMaterial>> MaterialsRenderThread;
2004 for (TRefCountPtr<TMaterial>& Material : Materials)
2005 {
2006 FMaterial* MaterialToDestroy = Material.GetReference();
2007 MaterialToDestroy->PrepareDestroy_GameThread();
2008 MaterialsRenderThread.Emplace(MoveTemp(Material));
2009 }
2010
2011 Materials.Empty();
2012 DeleteMaterialsOnRenderThread(MaterialsRenderThread);
2013 }
2014 }
2015
2016 template<typename TMaterial>
2017 static void DeferredDeleteArray(TArray<TMaterial*>& Materials)
2018 {
2019 if (Materials.Num() > 0)
2020 {
2021 TArray<TRefCountPtr<FMaterial>> MaterialsRenderThread;
2022 for (FMaterial* Material : Materials)
2023 {
2024 Material->PrepareDestroy_GameThread();
2025 MaterialsRenderThread.Emplace(Material);
2026 }
2027
2028 Materials.Empty();
2029 DeleteMaterialsOnRenderThread(MaterialsRenderThread);
2030 }
2031 }

2049 }

2053#endif

2381 /** Returns whether this material should be considered for casting dynamic shadows. */
2382 inline bool ShouldCastDynamicShadows() const
2383 {
2384 const EBlendMode BlendMode = GetBlendMode();
2385 return !GetShadingModels().HasOnlyShadingModel(MSM_SingleLayerWater) &&
2386 (IsOpaqueBlendMode(BlendMode)
2387 || IsMaskedBlendMode(BlendMode)
2388 || (IsTranslucentOnlyBlendMode(BlendMode) && GetCastDynamicShadowAsMasked()));
2389 }

2522 /**
2523 * Finds the shader matching the template type and the passed in vertex factory, asserts if not found.
2524 * Note - Only implemented for FMeshMaterialShaderTypes
2525 */
2526 template<typename ShaderType>
2527 TShaderRef<ShaderType> GetShader(FVertexFactoryType* VertexFactoryType, const typename ShaderType::FPermutationDomain& PermutationVector, bool bFatalIfMissing = true) const
2528 {
2529 return GetShader<ShaderType>(VertexFactoryType, PermutationVector.ToDimensionValueId(), bFatalIfMissing);
2530 }
2531
2532 template <typename ShaderType>
2533 TShaderRef<ShaderType> GetShader(FVertexFactoryType* VertexFactoryType, int32 PermutationId = 0, bool bFatalIfMissing = true) const
2534 {
2535 return TShaderRef<ShaderType>::Cast(GetShader(&ShaderType::GetStaticType(), VertexFactoryType, PermutationId, bFatalIfMissing));
2536 }

2757 /**
2758 * Game thread tracked shader map, which is ref counted and manages shader map lifetime.
2759 * The shader map uses deferred deletion so that the rendering thread has a chance to process a release command when the shader map is no longer referenced.
2760 * Code that sets this is responsible for updating RenderingThreadShaderMap in a thread safe way.
2761 * During an async compile, this will be NULL and will not contain the actual shader map until compilation is complete.
2762 */
2763 TRefCountPtr<FMaterialShaderMap> GameThreadShaderMap;

3131/**
3132 * This class takes care of all of the details you need to worry about when modifying a UMaterial
3133 * on the main thread. This class should *always* be used when doing so!
3134 */
3135class FMaterialUpdateContext
3136{
3137 /** UMaterial parents of any UMaterialInterfaces updated within this context. */
3138 TSet<UMaterial*> UpdatedMaterials;
3139 /** Materials updated within this context. */
3140 TSet<UMaterialInterface*> UpdatedMaterialInterfaces;
3141 /** Active global component reregister context, if any. */
3142 TUniquePtr<class FGlobalComponentReregisterContext> ComponentReregisterContext;
3143 /** Active global component render state recreation context, if any. */
3144 TUniquePtr<class FGlobalComponentRecreateRenderStateContext> ComponentRecreateRenderStateContext;
3145 /** The shader platform that was being processed - can control if we need to update components */
3146 EShaderPlatform ShaderPlatform;
3147 /** True if the SyncWithRenderingThread option was specified. */
3148 bool bSyncWithRenderingThread;
3149
3150public:
3151
3152 /** Options controlling what is done before/after the material is updated. */
3153 struct EOptions
3154 {
3155 enum Type
3156 {
3157 /** Reregister all components while updating the material. */
3158 ReregisterComponents = 0x1,
3159 /**
3160 * Sync with the rendering thread. This is necessary when modifying a
3161 * material exposed to the rendering thread. You may omit this flag if
3162 * you have already flushed rendering commands.
3163 */
3164 SyncWithRenderingThread = 0x2,
3165 /* Recreates only the render state for all components (mutually exclusive with ReregisterComponents) */
3166 RecreateRenderStates = 0x4,
3167 /** Default options: Recreate render state, sync with rendering thread. */
3168 Default = RecreateRenderStates | SyncWithRenderingThread,
3169 };
3170 };
3171
3172 /** Initialization constructor. */
3173 explicit ENGINE_API FMaterialUpdateContext(uint32 Options = EOptions::Default, EShaderPlatform InShaderPlatform = GMaxRHIShaderPlatform);
3174
3175 /** Destructor. */
3176 ENGINE_API ~FMaterialUpdateContext();
3177
3178 /** Add a material that has been updated to the context. */
3179 ENGINE_API void AddMaterial(UMaterial* Material);
3180
3181 /** Adds a material instance that has been updated to the context. */
3182 ENGINE_API void AddMaterialInstance(UMaterialInstance* Instance);
3183
3184 /** Adds a material interface that has been updated to the context. */
